<subSubSection id="748C08FAFF88500237A897FE0111928B" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3C295B71FF88500237A897FE0287921B" blockId="6.[151,1437,923,1203]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF88500237A897FE0247958F" bold="true" box="[151,274,923,950]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lateral oral margins not produced. Scutum mainly long yellow pilose, except for posteromedial patches of black pile. Scutellum with deeply concave posterior margin, without calcars. Basotarsomere of proleg about 1.5 times as wide as apex of protibia. Postero-apical corner of cell r 
<subScript id="A0125934FF885002346697900026923A" attach="left" box="[857,883,1013,1027]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">4+5</subScript>
rounded, without outward appendix. Length ratio of terga III–IV is about 1: 2.
</paragraph>
